Quoted By: >>15722175
>>15722080
Real Robot usually tries to be somewhat realistic and is usually quite military focused, treating the mechs as another type of military hardware. Examples might include Mechwarrior or Armoured Trooper Votoms.

Super Robot gives zero shits about realism and is usually more analogues to super heroes, super robots often do not respect conservation of mass, have super moves that the pilot shouts the names of and are often compared to gods. Examples might include Mazinger Z or Gurren Lagann.

Anonymous Sat 12 May 2018 14:08:29 No.15722990 Report
Quoted By: >>15723008 >>15723047
At the people who seemed to dislike Pastebin, I just wanted to clarify why some of us find it useful. At least it's how I see it.

Posting on SoFurry or FurAffinity is basically telling people "The story is finished, fully and for all time. No more edits will be made, unless it's far down the road." Especially on SF. It's like the e621 of written material. The go-to archive.

Places like Archive of our Own or Hentai Foundry is far more... "I wrote something, but it's just whatever."

Whereas Pastebin is even lower. It's like a sketchbook for words. I can post things there comfortably even though I'm never satisfied that the mad scribblings that I'm trying to coerce into becoming a story will ever actually be a story.
